      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY BREAD ROLL (5) tackled far tougher grade latest when finishing 4th over 520m at Wentworth Park. Scored at Gunnedah in weaker company the previous run. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. HOMER MULWEE (2) boasts a strong record this journey here with seven wins and four minors from 17 tries. Scored by 1.5 lengths last time (22.92) in a Grade 5 over 400m at this track. Among the main chances. RED AURA (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 1.5 lengths at this track in a handy 23.02 beating Chutzpah. Has performed well from this box with a win and six minor placings to his name from nine starts. Can make it two on the bounce. SEMI PEAKIN' (7) was in the money last start and poses a threat again.",
